<UserControl x:Class="LNStone.Views.LNAbout"
             xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" 
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008" 
             xmlns:local="clr-namespace:LNStone.Views"
             mc:Ignorable="d" 
             d:DesignHeight="600" d:DesignWidth="700" Margin="10,10">
    <Grid>
        <ScrollViewer>
        <StackPanel Margin="30,30">

                <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource MaterialDesignHeadline4TextBlock}"
                           TextWrapping="Wrap"
                           LineStackingStrategy="MaxHeight"
                           LineHeight="60">
        ABOUT THE PROGRAM AND THE CREATOR
            </TextBlock>
                <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource MaterialDesignHeadline5TextBlock}"
                           TextWrapping="Wrap"
                           LineStackingStrategy="MaxHeight"
                           LineHeight="20">
        Why was this program created?<LineBreak></LineBreak>
            </TextBlock>
         
                <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource MaterialDesignSubtitle1TextBlock}"
                           TextWrapping="Wrap"
                           LineStackingStrategy="MaxHeight"
                           LineHeight="20">
                I wrote this little program with my fiancée in mind.
                As a hobby, she creates various types of jewelry for friends using semi-precious stones for this purpose,
                such as: semi-precious and precious stones, surgical steel, threads, strings, cabochons ...
                state that the manufacturer is limited only by his imagination. And maybe a pocket sometimes.
                Some of her works can be seen in the "Gallery" tab or through the "Instagram" tab.<LineBreak></LineBreak>
                </TextBlock>

                <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource MaterialDesignHeadline5TextBlock}"
                           TextWrapping="Wrap"
                           LineStackingStrategy="MaxHeight"
                           LineHeight="20">
        What is this program for?<LineBreak></LineBreak>
                </TextBlock>

                <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource MaterialDesignSubtitle2TextBlock}"
                           TextWrapping="Wrap"
                           LineStackingStrategy="MaxHeight"
                           LineHeight="30">
        The general assumption is that this program will allow:
                </TextBlock>

                <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource MaterialDesignSubtitle1TextBlock}"
                           TextWrapping="Wrap"
                           LineStackingStrategy="MaxHeight"
                           LineHeight="30">
                - creating a database of purchased items,<LineBreak></LineBreak>
                - calculating the cost of purchasing materials needed to make, for example, a bracelet,<LineBreak></LineBreak>
                - calculating a margin on sales (it is known that family and friends are always on a low threshold),<LineBreak></LineBreak>
                - shopping in one of your favorite stores,<LineBreak></LineBreak>
                - social media management.<LineBreak></LineBreak>
                </TextBlock>

                <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource MaterialDesignSubtitle2TextBlock}"
                           TextWrapping="Wrap"
                           LineStackingStrategy="MaxHeight"
                           LineHeight="30">
        I want to add in the near future:
                </TextBlock>

                <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource MaterialDesignSubtitle1TextBlock}"
                           TextWrapping="Wrap"
                           LineStackingStrategy="MaxHeight"
                           LineHeight="30">
                - the ability to add photos to the gallery,<LineBreak></LineBreak>
                - photo captions informing what elements were used to make a given jewelery.<LineBreak></LineBreak>
                </TextBlock>

                <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource MaterialDesignHeadline5TextBlock}"
                           TextWrapping="Wrap"
                           LineStackingStrategy="MaxHeight"
                           LineHeight="20">
        Afterwords.<LineBreak></LineBreak>
                </TextBlock>

                <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource MaterialDesignSubtitle1TextBlock}"
                           TextWrapping="Wrap"
                           LineStackingStrategy="MaxHeight"
                           LineHeight="20">
                If you have a similar hobby / job and have any suggestions on what could be added to the program or found a bug,
                please contact:<LineBreak></LineBreak><LineBreak></LineBreak>
                AdalbertS@protonmail.com
                </TextBlock>
                
        </StackPanel>
        </ScrollViewer>
    </Grid>
</UserControl>
